The most popular size refers to the size with the highest sales count within each brand and fit; 
Total sales revenue is the sum of the total amount of all orders for each brand;
Top-size total sales refer to the total sales count of the most popular size for each brand.

- A 'top-performing product' refers to the product with the highest sales within a specific garment type and size category.; 
- 'Price range' is calculated as the minimum price (actual price) and the maximum price (actual price plus 20% of the actual price).; 
- The 'key measurement' refers to the measurement that is most relevant to the garment type, as determined by the measurements table.; 
- A 'garment type' can have multiple sizes and measurements associated with it.
